	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yup, another bit question, lol!<br /><br />I'd like to know, how do I look at a register, check each individual bit, and if each bit I come across is not equal, I want to simply inc a random register.<br /><br />Like.<br /><br />LDA $C0<br />(perform bit compare)<br />(if not equal, branch to INC  $C1<br />(loop back to compare)<br /><br />That's my assumption, I'm just kind of in the dark on how to loop back. Do I set either y/x with 07, and Dec to 00 then end my routine? Thanks for reading! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
