	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: How do i check all 8 individual bits within a register?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This sounds similar to checking parity, except in that case the result would be only bit 0 of that variable that was incremented (which tells if you have an even or odd number of bits).<br /><br />Some code would look like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;lda #0<br />&nbsp;sta count<br />&nbsp;ldx #8<br />&nbsp;lda var1<br /><br />@loop:<br />&nbsp;asl<br />&nbsp;bcc @skip&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; change to BCS if you want to count number of '0' bits instead<br />&nbsp;inc count<br />@skip:<br />&nbsp;dex<br />&nbsp;bne @loop<br /></div><br /><br />edit: derp

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


